## Beaconchain Dashboard

Beaconchain Dashboard is an open-source Ethereum 2.0 validator performance tracker app for Android and iOS. It uses the beaconcha.in API.

Author: Mahdi Amolimoghaddam

---

### Features
- Track validator online status, balances, rewards and more  
- Configurable notification alerts per validator  
- Combined dashboard view (supports up to 100 validators)  
- Ethereum client update notifications and network warnings  
- Support for multiple fiat currencies  
- Mainnet and Testnet support  
- Add validators via public key, index, or ETH1 deposit address  
- Light and Dark themes

---

### Technologies
- Angular (TypeScript, HTML, CSS)  
- Ionic Framework and Ionic Capacitor for native bridging

---

### Prerequisites
- Node.js and npm  
- Ionic CLI, native-run and cordova-res:
```
npm install -g @ionic/cli native-run cordova-res
```
- Install project dependencies:
```
npm i
```
- Note: You must provide your own google-services.json (Android) and GoogleService-Info.plist (iOS).

Android
- Android Studio (recommended 4.1.1 or newer) with Android SDK
- On Linux, adjust linuxAndroidStudioPath in capacitor.config.json if needed

iOS
- macOS Catalina or newer
- Xcode 12.2 or newer

---

### Development / Run in Browser
Start a local development server with live reload:
```
ionic serve
```

---

### Run on Android (Livereload)
Build the app once, then run with livereload:
```
ionic build
ionic capacitor run android --livereload --external --host=YOUR_IP --disableHostCheck
```
Replace YOUR_IP with your computer’s local IP. Ensure port 8100 is accessible.

Build for production:
```
ionic capacitor run android --prod --release
```

Install via Android Studio or run on emulator per Android docs.

---

### Run on iOS (Livereload)
Build the app once, then run with livereload:
```
ionic build
ionic capacitor run ios --livereload --external --host=YOUR_IP --disableHostCheck
```
Replace YOUR_IP with your Mac’s local IP. Ensure port 8100 is accessible.

Build for production:
```
ionic capacitor run ios --prod --release
```

---

### Best Practices
- Use reusable components for shared UI across pages.  
- Use Angular pipes for currency conversion and value formatting.  
- Support light/dark themes using CSS variables. See src/app/theme/variables.scss and src/app/global.scss.

---

### Folder / Commands Quick Reference
- Install dependencies:
```
npm i
```
- Start dev server:
```
ionic serve
```
- Build:
```
ionic build
```
- Android prod build:
```
